[quote] RIZZO _*.*_ VINE VOICE

Wow! This CD collection features the best in mariachi music, the classics with an enhanced sound. This historical musical collection dates back to 1933 and the instruments play fabulous! There are numerous instruments that enhance these popular mariachi favorites, such as "El Mariachi", "Feria de las Flores", "Jesucita en Chihuahua", "Alle en Rancho Grande" "El Realera" and of course "Cancion Mixteca". There are more great traditional classics

You will hear harps, bells, and different trumpets, guitars, etc., At times it is so orchestral yet that mariachi rhythm and feeling is always present. And, there are no vocals to respond to, just music.

There isn't much info that comes with this CD, but some linear notes are written in Spanish.

Sit back, relax, crank up the stereo and prepare for a soothing and wonderful listening experience to mariachi. Rizzo[/quote]
